Mercedes Plans 10 New Models by 2020, Automotive News Reports

-- B y   C h r i s   R e i t e r
-- 
2011-09-03T14:44:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-03/mercedes-plans-10-new-models-by-2020-automotive-news-reports.html
Daimler AG (DAI) ’s Mercedes-Benz plans to
introduce at least 10 new models by 2020 to meet its goal of
becoming the largest and most profitable maker of  luxury
vehicles ,  Automotive News Europe  reported, citing an interview
with Chief Executive Officer Dieter Zetsche.  Daimler is sticking to its forecast to sell more than 1.35
million cars in 2011 and is confident it can deliver more cars
than  Volkswagen AG (VOW) ’s Audi over the full year, the newspaper
said.  The Stuttgart, Germany-based manufacturer will adhere to
its plan to achieve an operating profit for the Mercedes cars
unit equivalent to 10 percent of sales, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Reiter in Berlin at 
